</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsect1>
<title>Configuring Gegl from CVS on Unix-like Systems</title>

<para>
Once you have the source code and prerequisites, cd to the main top level 
Gegl directory and run the script <filename>autogen.sh</filename> which is found there:
<programlisting>
$ ./autogen.sh
</programlisting>
</para>
<para>
This script is roughly equivalent to the following: 
<programlisting>
$ aclocal 
$ automake
$ autoconf
$ ./configure
</programlisting>
</para>
<para>
The shell script called <filename>configure</filename> makes the template
makefiles called <filename>Makefile.in</filename> in the package and creates
makefiles customized for your operating system. 
</para>

<para>
If you want to add options to <filename>configure</filename>,
you can do so by passing them directly to
<filename>autogen.sh</filename>, they will be passed on to
<filename>configure</filename>.
For example if you want to enable building the gtk-docs for
gegl, you can use the <systemitem>--enable-gtk-doc</systemitem> argument which
causes the gtk-docs for gegl to be built:
<programlisting>
$ ./configure --enable-gtk-doc
</programlisting>
</para>
<para>
A full list of options you can pass can be found by running
<filename>configure</filename> with the
<systemitem>--help</systemitem> argument. In general, the defaults should 
work fine. 
</para>
</refsect1>

